Preheat oven to 350 degrees F Cut off the blossom end of the zucchini. Grate until you have 1 cup worth (loosely packed). Place in a medium sized bowl and add the salt. Toss and let sit for a couple of minutes. Squeeze the zukes to encourage them to give up some of their juices. Add the Just Whites and beat into the liquids with a fork. Add the cream, vanilla extract, cinnamon and baking powder. Blend well. To get 1/2 cup of finely chopped walnuts, put about 2/3 cup of walnut pieces into a food processor until about 1/3 of the walnuts are almost flour and the rest are no bigger than about this - O. Add the wheat bran, whey powder, Splenda and walnuts. Stir well. Alternatively, pour the batter into a small bread loaf pan and bake for 20-30 minutes. Insert 6 parchment paper baking cups into a muffin tin. Spoon batter into the cups dividing evenly (each about 3/4 full). Bake at 350 degrees F for 15-20 minutes until tops start to brown. Cool for 5-10 minutes before adding the icing. Alternatively, pour the batter into a small bread loaf pan and bake for 20-30 minutes. Meanwhile, make the icing. Soften the cream cheese by zapping it in the microwave for about 30 seconds. Stir in the cream, vanilla and Splenda. Stir until smooth. Ice the cupcakes once they have cooled. I like to keep them in the paper because they stay moist longer. Store extras in Tupperware in the refrigerator